  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Testpilot generates javascript tests with ChatGPT 3.5 using a 0-shot test prompt and then iteratively adds additional code and documentation context if the generated tests fail(arxiv) [32].",
    "ChatUnitTest generates tests using adaptive focal context based on the maximum focal length and then applies both rules-based repair and self-debugging based on error messages when generated tests fail [40].",
    "ChatTester similarly generates tests based on the focal context and then prompts ChatGPT with error messages when generated tests fail(arxiv) [43].",
    "These approaches all focus on constructing the focal context and then fixing ChatGPT's generations.",
    "In contrast our work focuses on developing prompts to guide the model to test each execution path in the focal method, improving testsuite coverage."
  ],
